<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id627e68e2-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1804"><num value="1804">§ 1804.</num><heading> Eligible grant recipients</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">To be eligible for assistance under this subchapter, a tribally controlled college or university must be one which—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id627e68e3-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1804/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> is governed by a board of directors or board of trustees a majority of which are Indians;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id627e68e4-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1804/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> demonstrates adherence to stated goals, a philosophy, or a plan of operation which is directed to meet the needs of Indians;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id627e68e5-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1804/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> if in operation for more than one year, has students a majority of whom are Indians; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id627e68e6-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1804/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id627e68e7-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1804/4/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> is accredited by a nationally recognized accrediting agency or association determined by the Secretary of Education to be a reliable authority with regard to the quality of training offered; or</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id627e68e8-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1804/4/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> according to such an agency or association, is making reasonable progress toward accreditation.</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id627e68e9-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/471/tI/s103">Pub. L. 95–471, title I, § 103</ref>, <date date="1978-10-17">Oct. 17, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1326">92 Stat. 1326</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/105/244/tIX/s901/b/5">Pub. L. 105–244, title IX, § 901(b)(5)</ref>, <date date="1998-10-07">Oct. 7, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1828">112 Stat. 1828</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/110/315/tIX/s941/d">Pub. L. 110–315, title IX, § 941(d)</ref>, <date date="2008-08-14">Aug. 14, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/3461">122 Stat. 3461</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
